Post title: Questionnaire Redirecting
Post description: Theme is Adaptable Release 4.0.1.2, version 2022051205 on Moodle 4.0.3+ (Build: 20220902) PHP Version 7.4.32, database mysql (5.7.40) Questionnaire version mod_questionnaire_moodle40_2021062301 My level of ability: Proficient+ with Moodle user functions, novice with Linux and php scripts, but have been around IT for a long time so good at following directions and digging around. Issue: Questionnaires which worked before update from 3.11 to 4.0 now redirect to https://domainname/my/. Questionnaire settings can be accessed, modified, and saved. Questionnaires can be found in the database. New questionnaires can be created and they appear in the database. Things attempted: - Looked at server php.error.log, log which has the traffic ("GET" and "POST" records), and every other error log file I could find on the server. There are no recent php errors, and you can see the requests for the questionnaire instances. - Went through the questionnaire/view.php files from the old working instance and this one. I do not have a strong background in the code, but it seems that in the line calling for the questionnaire, the variable parameters passed are in a different order. I figured this was not an issue, as when I checked to see on the Moodle plugins download site to see if people were using the plugin successfully, it seems like a lot of people have it running on 4.0 and 4.1. - Reinstalled the questionnaire files. It was the same version as before, as our update to 4.0 was after this plugin was last updated. - I cannot easily edit the php.ini file due to hosting server limitations. Followed the recommendations here: https://moodle.org/mod/forum/discuss.php?d=316343 to change the config.php file. The final lines in the file now read 
```text
@ini_set('log_errors', 'on');
@ini_set('error_log', '/error/err_log.txt');
@ini_set('error_reporting', E_ALL);

require_once(__DIR__ . '/lib/setup.php');

// There is no php closing tag in this file,
// it is intentional because it prevents trailing whitespace problems!
```
 Where err_log.txt is a file I created in the moodle/error/ folder. Permissions on the file are 0666 and the folder 0755. After creating the file, I purged caches and attempted to open a questionnaire. The redirect still happened. Nothing was written to the err_log.txt. Server phpinfo.php says that the following values are set: Directive Local Value Master Value error_log /error/err_log.txt error_log log_errors On On Questions: Has anyone encountered this before? Were you able to fix it, and if so, how? Does anyone in general have suggestions as to what to try next? Have I set up error logging correctly?
